If you add this to your app delegate, iRate will never prompt automatically:

```
+ (void)initialize
{
    [iRate sharedInstance].promptAtLaunch = NO;
}
```

If you can't find or reproduce the problem, your best option is probably to disable the automatic display of iRate on launch by adding this to AppDelegate

```
- (void)initialize {
    [iRate sharedInstance].promptAtLaunch  = NO;
}
```

Then, when you get to a safe point in the app, call

```
[[iRate sharedInstance] promptIfAllCriteriaMet];
```

Which will show the rating dialog, but only if all the criteria you've set have been met (number of days installed, etc).

